## Mental model

Plugins contribute capabilities through a manifest.

The host reads `netscript.config.ts`.

The host resolves each plugin manifest.

The host merges contribution axes.

The host runs the walker.

The walker emits generated registries.

Generated registries live under `.netscript/generated`.

User code stays in normal project folders.

The plugin package owns plugin semantics.

The framework owns host wiring.

## API

The root entrypoint exports the manifest.

`./cli` runs the plugin command tree.

`./scaffolding` is reserved for item scaffolding helpers.

`./e2e` returns plugin e2e gates.

`./aspire` contributes Aspire resources.

`./testing` contains fixtures for downstream tests.

